history.content:
Yeah I highly recommend this combo if you like lin alg and planning to take courses like 127 and 189 in the future.

I’m doing these two classes right now. You can get an abstract, proof-based, high level understanding of linear map from 110, and see how it can be applied in reality from 16B. 

It may seem like they are talking about the same content and be redundant, but they are seeing things in a completely different way. For example, we don’t even write out a single matrix during the midterm in this semester’s 110. But matrix is everywhere in 16B.

The content of Mid2 for these two classes are somehow overlapped and I believe final too.

Yeah I highly recommend this combo if you like lin alg and planning to take courses like 127 and 189 in the future.
